[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s854"},"text":"34 U.S.C. 854","children":[],"tail":" (note)."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1952-07-09/ch608/s803"},"text":"July 9, 1952, ch. 608, § 803","children":[],"tail":" (2d sentence of 1st par.), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/66/505"},"text":"66 Stat. 505","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s854c"},"text":"34 U.S.C. 854c","children":[],"tail":" (less 4th, 5th, 6th (as applicable to "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s854b"},"text":"34 U.S.C. 854b","children":[],"tail":") and 7th provisos)."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1938-06-25/ch690/s204"},"text":"June 25, 1938, ch. 690, § 204","children":[],"tail":" (less 4th, 5th, 6th (as applicable to § 203 of the Naval Reserve Act of 1938), and 7th provisos), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/52/1170"},"text":"52 Stat. 1170","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1946-08-10/ch952/s2"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1946, ch. 952, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/993"},"text":"60 Stat. 993","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s854a"},"text":"34 U.S.C. 854a","children":[],"tail":" (less provisos)."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1938-06-25/ch690/s202"},"text":"June 25, 1938, ch. 690, § 202","children":[],"tail":" (less provisos), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/52/1178"},"text":"52 Stat. 1178","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a) the words “officers” and “assigned” are omitted, since they are applicable only to the proviso in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s854"},"text":"34 U.S.C. 854","children":[],"tail":", which is recommended for repeal as obsolete. (See Table 2A.) The words “including (a) those former members of the Fleet Reserve who were transferred * * * but before the expiration of three months following discharge”, appearing in § 803 of the Armed Forces Reserve Act of 1952, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/66/505"},"text":"66 Stat. 505","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s854"},"text":"34 U.S.C. 854","children":[],"tail":" (note)) are omitted as surplusage. These words merely illustrate the class of persons transferred to the Fleet Reserve under the Naval Reserve Act of 1938, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/52/1178"},"text":"52 Stat. 1178","children":[],"tail":", as referred to in the section from which these words were taken, and in no way limit that class or impose a citizenship requirement for membership in it. (See the opinion of the Judge Advocate General of the Navy, JAG:II:1:JFG:imz of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1953-02-17"},"text":"February 17, 1953","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b) reference to the date ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1925-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1925","children":[],"tail":", is omitted, since members who were in the naval service on or before that date may, if they are qualified and so elect, be transferred to the Fleet Reserve or to the Fleet Marine Corps Reserve under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s854c"},"text":"34 U.S.C. 854c","children":[],"tail":" instead of under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s854b"},"text":"34 U.S.C. 854b","children":[],"tail":", as provided in the fifth proviso of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s854c"},"text":"34 U.S.C. 854c","children":[],"tail":". That proviso and the provisions of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s854b"},"text":"34 U.S.C. 854b","children":[],"tail":", which are applicable only to persons who were in the naval service in 1925, are not codified because they relate to a small closed class and are therefore of limited interest. They are not repealed, however. (See Table 2D.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsections (b) and (c) the term “active service in the armed forces” is substituted for the term “active Federal service” to execute the definition in the last sentence of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s854c"},"text":"34 U.S.C. 854c","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (c) the words “is entitled, when not on active duty, to retainer pay at the rate of 2½ percent of the basic pay that he received at the time of transfer” are substituted for the words “except when on active duty, shall be paid at the annual rate of 2½ per centum of the annual base and longevity pay they are receiving at the time of transfer” to conform to the terminology of the Career Compensation Act of 1949 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t37/s231"},"text":"37 U.S.C. 231","children":[],"tail":" et seq.)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (d) states the rule as to the method of counting minority and short-term enlistments, in connection with determining active service, in accordance with ","children":[{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"White v. United States","children":[],"tail":", 97 F. Supp. 698."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idab1ecfe2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idab1ecfe3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/s807/b/15"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, § 807(b)(15)","children":[],"tail":", renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s6330"},"text":"section 6330 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/s809/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, § 809(a)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section 8333” for “section 6333”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2006—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/163"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–163","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Navy Reserve” for “Naval Reserve”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1989—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/189"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–189","children":[],"tail":" substituted “under this section.” for “under—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(1) Title II of the Naval Reserve Act of 1938 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/52/1178"},"text":"52 Stat. 1178","children":[],"tail":"), as amended; or"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(2) this section.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—Subsec. (c)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/348/s203/b/6/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–348, § 203(b)(6)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted provision that retainer pay be computed under section 6333 for provision that retainer pay, in the case of a member who first became a member of a uniformed service, as defined in section 1407(a)(2), before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-09-08"},"text":"Sept. 8, 1980","children":[],"tail":", be at the rate of 2½ percent of the basic pay that he received at the time of transfer or, in the case of a member who served as master chief petty officer of the Navy or sergeant major of the Marine Corps, of the highest basic pay to which he was entitled while so serving, if that basic pay is higher than the basic pay received at the time of transfer, or in the case of a member who first became a member of a uniformed service, as defined in section 1407(a)(2), on or after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-09-08"},"text":"Sept. 8, 1980","children":[],"tail":", be at the rate of 2½ percent of the monthly retainer pay base computed under section 1407(d), which rates were to be multiplied by the number of years of active service in the armed forces."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/348/s203/b/6/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–348, § 203(b)(6)(B)","children":[],"tail":", struck out par. (4) which provided that in no case could a member’s retainer pay be more than 75 percent of the basic pay or monthly retainer pay base upon which computation of retainer pay was based."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/348/s305/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–348, § 305(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", designated existing provisions as par. (1), struck out provision that a completed minority enlistment be counted as four years of active service and an enlistment terminated within three months before the end of the term be counted as active service for the full term, and added pars. (2) and (3)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1983—Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/94"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–94","children":[],"tail":" substituted “For the purposes of subsection (c), each full month of service that is in addition to the number of full years of service creditable to a member is counted as one-twelfth of a year and any remaining fractional part of a month is disregarded” for “For the purposes of subsections (b) and (c), a part of a year that is six months or more is counted as a whole year and a part of a year that is less than six months is disregarded”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/513"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–513","children":[],"tail":" substituted “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-09-08"},"text":"September 8, 1980","children":[],"tail":"” for “the date of the enactment of the Department of Defense Authorization Act, 1981” wherever appearing, and “master chief petty officer” for “senior enlisted advisor”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/342"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–342","children":[],"tail":" amended subsec. (c) generally, designating existing provisions as pars. (1) to (4) and, as so amended, in par. (1) designated existing provisions as subpar. (A), as so designated, inserted provision limiting applicability to persons who became members of the uniformed services before the date of the enactment of the Department of Defense Authorization Act, 1981, and added subpar. (B), in par. (2) inserted reference to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1402a"},"text":"section 1402a of this title","children":[],"tail":", and in par. (4) added applicability to monthly retainer pay base."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1967—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/207"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–207","children":[],"tail":" inserted “, except that in the case of a member who has served as senior enlisted advisor of the Navy or sergeant major of the Marine Corps, retainer pay shall be computed on the basis of the highest basic pay to which he was entitled while so serving, if that basic pay is higher than the basic pay received at the time of transfer” after “armed forces”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1958—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/583/s1/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–583, § 1(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “naval service” for “Regular Navy and the Regular Marine Corps, respectively,”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/583/s1/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–583, § 1(3)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “or the Naval Reserve” after “Regular Navy” and “or the Marine Corps Reserve” after “Regular Marine Corps”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idab1ecfe4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idab1ecfe5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2018 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2019-02-01"},"text":"Feb. 1, 2019","children":[],"tail":", with provision for the coordination of amendments and special rule for certain redesignations, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/s800"},"text":"section 800 of Pub. L. 115–232","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3001"},"text":"section 3001 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idab1ecfe6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1983 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/94"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–94","children":[],"tail":" applicable with respect to the computation of retired or retainer pay of any individual who becomes entitled to that pay after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-09-30"},"text":"Sept. 30, 1983","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/94/s923/g"},"text":"section 923(g) of Pub. L. 98–94","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1174"},"text":"section 1174 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idab1ecfe7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1980 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/513"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–513","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-12-12"},"text":"Dec. 12, 1980","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/513/s701/b/3"},"text":"section 701(b)(3) of Pub. L. 96–513","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s101"},"text":"section 101 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idab1ecfe8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1967 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/207"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–207","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1967-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1967","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/207/s7"},"text":"section 7 of Pub. L. 90–207","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t37/s203"},"text":"section 203 of Title 37","children":[],"tail":", Pay and Allowances of the Uniformed Services."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idab1ecfe9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Temporary Early Retirement Authority","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For provisions authorizing the Secretary of the Navy, during the period beginning ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-23"},"text":"Oct. 23, 1992","children":[],"tail":", and ending "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1995-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1995","children":[],"tail":", to apply this section to an enlisted member of the Navy or Marine Corps with at least 15 but less than 20 years of service by substituting “15 or more years” for “20 or more years” in the first sentence of subsection (a) [probably should be (b)] of this section and in the second sentence of subsec. (b) of this section, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/484/s4403"},"text":"section 4403 of Pub. L. 102–484","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1293"},"text":"section 1293 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idab1ecfea-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Former Members of Navy or Marine Corps to Fleet Reserve or Fleet Marine Corps Reserve; Transfer to Retired List","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-07-24/ch683"},"text":"Act July 24, 1956, ch. 683","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70/626"},"text":"70 Stat. 626","children":[],"tail":", provided: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/act/1956-07-24/ch683"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"section","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":""},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"“Upon application by any former member of the Navy or Marine Corps—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" who was discharged prior to ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1946-08-10"},"text":"August 10, 1946","children":[],"tail":", under honorable conditions, and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" who, at the time of his discharge, had at least twenty years’ active Federal service,","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"the Secretary of the Navy shall appoint such former member in the Fleet Reserve or Fleet Marine Corps Reserve, as may be appropriate, in the rank held by him at the time of such discharge.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"section","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“Sec. 2.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Each person appointed to the Fleet Reserve or Fleet Marine Corps Reserve under the first section of this Act shall be transferred to the appropriate retired list (1) on the first day of the first calendar month beginning after such appointment, if his last discharge occurred ten or more years prior to the date of such appointment, and (2) in the case of individuals appointed under such section before the expiration of ten years from their last discharge, on the first day of the first calendar month, beginning after the expiration of ten years from the date of such discharge.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"section","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"“Sec. 3.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Each former member transferred to a retired list under clauses (1) and (2) of section 2 shall receive retired pay at the annual rate of 2½ per centum of the annual base and longevity pay he was receiving at the time of his last discharge, multiplied by the number of his years of active Federal service at such time (not to exceed thirty), and adjusted to reflect the percentage increases made since such discharge in the retired pay of persons retired from the Armed Forces prior to ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1949-10-12"},"text":"October 12, 1949","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"section","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"“Sec. 4.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" For the purposes of this Act, all active service in the Army of the United States, the Navy, the Marine Corps, the Coast Guard, or any component thereof, shall be deemed to be active Federal service.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"section","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"“Sec. 5.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" No pay shall accrue to the benefit of any person appointed under the provisions of this Act prior to the date such person is actually appointed under the provisions of this Act and in no event prior to the first day of the first month following enactment of this Act [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1956-07-24"},"text":"July 24, 1956","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
